body.p:
It is possible to add an icon, change the borders, change the colors, etc. of any
        hazardstatement, for example, to customize the attention hazards,
      add the following rules to your customization
        CSS:*[class ~= "hazard-d/hazardstatement"][type = "attention"] {
  border-width: 2px;
}
*[class ~= "hazard-d/hazardstatement"][type = "attention"],
*[class ~= "hazard-d/hazardstatement"][type = "attention"] td {
  border-color: #ff9900;
}

.hazardstatement .hazardstatement--attention {
  text-align: left;
  padding-left: 3em;
  background-position: .5em .3em;
  background-image: url("danger.svg");
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-color: #ff9900;
  border-color: #ff9900;
  color: black;
}The default icon size is 24px and its
        URL is relative to the CSS stylesheet.
